# M6 — visual verification of ANIM_CROUCH and ANIM_PRONE poses.
#
# Pre-implementation: BTN_CROUCH (S/Down) and BTN_PRONE (X) were
# detected at the platform layer but no gameplay code consumed them
# (no ANIM_CROUCH / ANIM_PRONE, no anim_id transition in
# mech_step_drive, no pose rules in pose_compute).
#
# Implementation:
#   - mech.h: added ANIM_CROUCH and ANIM_PRONE.
#   - mech_step_drive: prone_held / crouch_held set anim_id with
#     priority PRONE > CROUCH > RUN > STAND (JET / FALL still
#     override).
#   - mech_post_physics_anchor: pelvis_y_target = foot_y - chain*0.55
#     for CROUCH; foot_y - 14 for PRONE.
#   - snapshot_capture / snapshot_apply: SNAP_STATE_CROUCH /
#     SNAP_STATE_PRONE bits ride the wire.
#   - pose_compute: torso shortened in CROUCH; body laid horizontal
#     in PRONE; knees bent forward in CROUCH; legs swept backward
#     in PRONE.
#
# This single-mech test just walks through the four states for a
# visual sanity check (STAND, CROUCH, PRONE, back to STAND).

window 1280 720
seed   88 22
out    build/shots/m6_crouch_prone

loadout Trooper "Pulse Rifle" Sidearm Light Standard
spawn_at 640 920
mouse    1100 360

at  20 shot t020_standing
at  60 press crouch
at  90 shot t090_crouching
at 130 release crouch
at 140 shot t140_back_to_standing
at 160 press prone
at 200 shot t200_prone
at 240 release prone
at 260 shot t260_back_to_standing_again

contact_sheet pose_sheet cols 4
at 300 end
